==English==

===Etymology===
French [[cynosure]] "Ursa Minor; Polaris", from Latin [[Cynosura|Cynosūra]] "Ursa Minor", from Ancient Greek [[κυνόσουρα]] (cynosūra) "Ursa Minor", literally "dog's tail": [[κύων|κυνός]] (cynos) "dog's" + [[οὐρά]] (ūra) "tail".

